; UNSAT: 8-bit counter starting at 0, incrementing by 1 — can it reach 300?
; 300 > 255 so the counter wraps and never hits 300 (which doesn't fit in 8 bits)
; Actually 300 mod 256 = 44, so the counter WILL reach 44.
; Let's use: counter starts at 0, increments by 2 — can it reach an odd number (1)?
; Expected: UNSAT
1 sort bitvec 8
2 sort bitvec 1
3 zero 1
4 state 1 count
5 constd 1 2
6 add 1 4 5
7 next 1 4 6
8 init 1 4 3
9 one 1
10 eq 2 4 9
11 bad 10
